The paper describes a new algorithm for automatically extracting useful models from execution traces of a HW/SW system, which is a problem commonly studied in the software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) communities. The algorithm leverages modern program synthesis techniques, which are also studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer architecture (cs.AR) communities. Finally, the paper applies the approach to traces from a variety of sources, including virtual platforms and real-time systems, which suggests a potential application in the systems (cs.SY) community.
